research_municipality_step.notes: Grapevine, TX operates under a council-manager government system. The Mayor and six Council Members are elected at-large for three-year terms. The current Mayor, William D. Tate, has a term expiring in 2027. Council Member Duff O'Dell's term expires in 2026. Council Member Sean Shope was elected in 2025 and his term expires in 2028. Leon Leal is running unopposed for re-election in May 2025.
